WEBVTT

00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:06.010
Number three, To-Car, is coming after her,

00:00:06.010 --> 00:00:08.610
along with Jewel Spinel on the inside of
the track and Divinity on the outside!

00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:09.900
The Japanese Derby!

00:00:09.900 --> 00:00:11.610
There's less than 200 meters to go!

00:00:11.610 --> 00:00:12.750
They're speeding up so much...

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:14.240
Dia-chan, go for it!

00:00:14.570 --> 00:00:16.130
Win this, Dia.

00:00:16.130 --> 00:00:18.750
You'll secure the first Satono G1 victory!

00:00:18.750 --> 00:00:21.770
And now To-Car is closing the gap!

00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:24.590
The battle for the top is a dead heat
between number eight, Satono Diamond,

00:00:24.590 --> 00:00:26.750
and number three, To-Car, on the inside!

00:00:26.750 --> 00:00:28.140
It looks like To-Car might
have a slight edge.

00:00:28.140 --> 00:00:31.280
But Satono Diamond is gradually closing
the gap, like she's being pulled forward!

00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:32.930
It's Satono Diamond versus To-Car!

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:34.490
Satono Diamond and To-Car!

00:00:34.490 --> 00:00:36.310
And they cross the goal together!

00:00:37.010 --> 00:00:42.910
Was the winner To-Car, or number eight, Satono
Diamond?! They seemed just about tied!

00:00:42.910 --> 00:00:46.520
And number one, Divinity, was slightly
behind them in third place.

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:54.570
It looks like...

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
To-Car has won!

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
First

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
To-Car

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
Tokyo

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
Japanese Derby

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
Second

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.570
Satono Diamond

00:00:56.570 --> 00:00:59.080
The winner in the end is number 3, To-Car.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:00.330
I did it!

00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:01.580
This battle ended with a photo finish!

00:01:01.580 --> 00:01:06.920
Number eight, Satono Diamond, put up a
great fight but came a step short!

00:01:06.920 --> 00:01:07.720
Dia-chan...

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:11.390
It looks like the horse girl that has
taken the spotlight of this generation

00:01:11.390 --> 00:01:13.040
is To-Car!

00:01:52.420 --> 00:02:02.680
Umamusume

00:01:56.260 --> 00:02:02.680
Pretty Derby

00:03:06.470 --> 00:03:10.480
Episode 5
\hProving Oneself

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:10.770
I'm sorry, Dia-chan.

00:03:11.080 --> 00:03:14.250
If your horseshoe hadn't broken,
you definitely would've won.

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:16.640
You shouldn't get into "what ifs"
when it comes to competition.

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:17.700
But...

00:03:17.700 --> 00:03:20.010
It was only an eight centimeter difference.

00:03:20.380 --> 00:03:22.510
The Satono jinx...

00:03:22.510 --> 00:03:26.250
Something like "Satono horse
girls can't win G1 races," right?

00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:31.980
I don't like admitting it, but it's
easy to see where it comes from.

00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:33.150
In my case...

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:42.320
And then in this year's
Satsukishou, with Dia...

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:46.280
It's like God is actually trying
to keep us from winning.

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:47.510
It's all right.

00:03:47.510 --> 00:03:50.330
I'm going to prove that jinx wrong...

00:03:50.810 --> 00:03:53.400
when I win the Kikkashou.

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:57.050
Dia-chan...

00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:10.700
A heart that never gives in,
and a will that's unbreakable...

00:04:10.700 --> 00:04:13.180
Dia-chan really is amazing.

00:04:13.890 --> 00:04:15.910
Okay, my turn!

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:25.780
That was your best time yet, Kita-chan!

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:28.530
Really?! All right!

00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:31.760
Your speed and stamina have
both leveled up nicely.

00:04:32.620 --> 00:04:35.130
It seems your training has borne fruit.

00:04:35.130 --> 00:04:35.920
Yeah.

00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:38.750
After the Spring Tennoushou,
that's two G1 victories,

00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:41.260
and your running is a lot more confident now.

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:44.580
You might end up the star
of your generation, Kitasan.

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:46.470
Who, me?!

00:04:46.470 --> 00:04:50.040
Let's keep your momentum going and
bring home the Takarazuka Kinen!

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:51.100
R-Right!

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:53.820
The Takarazuka Kinen is my specialty,

00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:56.070
and since she's my apprentice,
this should be an easy win.

00:04:56.070 --> 00:04:58.850
Since when are you Kitasan's master?!

00:04:58.850 --> 00:05:01.610
What happens if she starts being
awful at entering the gate?!

00:05:02.290 --> 00:05:04.140
Where you headed, Kitasan?

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:07.240
I'm gonna head out for my road work!

00:05:07.770 --> 00:05:10.500
She already ran so much,
but is still going...

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.550
She seriously has no bottom to her stamina.

00:05:12.550 --> 00:05:13.370
Yeah.

00:05:13.370 --> 00:05:15.210
She made it over the wall after all.

00:05:15.210 --> 00:05:16.250
That's right.

00:05:23.530 --> 00:05:26.390
After the Spring Tennoushou
is the Takarazuka Kinen....

00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:28.490
I wonder how my running is doing.

00:05:32.390 --> 00:05:33.530
Hello!

00:05:33.530 --> 00:05:34.680
How are you?

00:05:34.680 --> 00:05:37.880
Excuse me, could you direct
me to the Hanshin Racecourse?

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:39.820
Okay, okay!

00:05:39.820 --> 00:05:41.190
Okay, okay...

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:42.790
Here!

00:05:42.790 --> 00:05:43.900
It's this way, then?

00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:45.200
Bye!

00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:47.360
Thank you ever so much.

00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:50.130
Have I gotten any stronger?

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:53.440
I think I might have!

00:05:53.440 --> 00:05:57.110
The monster who was sidelined with
distal tibial fractures in both legs

00:05:57.110 --> 00:06:01.290
will resurface this spring, and will
soon return to domestic G1 races.

00:06:01.290 --> 00:06:03.470
We've got Duramente-san, coming off a race

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:05.420
where she made her aims for
the Takarazuka Kinen clear,

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:10.260
along with Air Groove-san, a veteran runner
who has known her since an early age.

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:13.140
Live Broadcast
Special interview

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:13.140
Double Crown Horse Girl
An Encounter with Duramente!

00:06:10.260 --> 00:06:13.140
And now it's time for our
special live interview!

00:06:13.670 --> 00:06:16.020
Duramente's gonna be at
the Takarazuka Kinen?!

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:16.020
For real?

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:18.640
It's been nine months since
your unfortunate injury.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:31.030
Live Broadcast
Special interview

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:31.030
Double Crown Horse Girl
An Encounter with Duramente!

00:06:18.640 --> 00:06:21.860
And you demonstrated pretty clearly that
you're back by winning the Nakayama Kinen!

00:06:22.290 --> 00:06:26.780
After that came a race in
Dubai where, despite some trouble,

00:06:26.780 --> 00:06:29.300
you were able to challenge some
of the strongest horse girls

00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:31.030
in Europe and come out in second place!

00:06:31.030 --> 00:06:34.910
That's an amazing result for your first
overseas excursion, Duramente-san!

00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:36.130
It was second place.

00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:37.530
What's that?

00:06:37.910 --> 00:06:40.330
It was second place. That's not amazing.

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:43.080
Uh, but, still...

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:54.560
Live Broadcast
Special interview

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:54.560
Double Crown Horse Girl
An Encounter with Duramente!

00:06:43.080 --> 00:06:46.400
I believe she's saying that racing
against the finest horse girls

00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:48.200
from Europe was a very valuable experience,

00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:52.160
and that by winning second place,
she's feeling very confident.

00:06:52.160 --> 00:06:53.690
I-I see...

00:06:54.560 --> 00:06:59.790
Well, it looks like the Takarazuka Kinen
is your next choice for a race.

00:06:59.790 --> 00:07:02.880
What kind of running do
you have in store for all

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:04.940
your domestic fans who are
looking forward to it?

00:07:04.940 --> 00:07:05.950
I'll win.

00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:09.480
Uh, well... is that all?

00:07:09.480 --> 00:07:10.170
I'll win.

00:07:10.170 --> 00:07:14.150
She's saying that she's looking forward
to putting out another dominant victory

00:07:14.150 --> 00:07:15.830
with her further improved running.

00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:19.680
Out of all the horse girls
who my mother has instructed,

00:07:19.680 --> 00:07:21.710
Duramente has the most remarkable potential.

00:07:21.710 --> 00:07:24.160
I'm sure she'll put on a
race at the Takarazuka Kinen

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:25.850
that will surprise all the fans.

00:07:25.850 --> 00:07:28.960
I see. Well, I'm looking forward to it!

00:07:28.960 --> 00:07:31.650
Now, regarding the Takarazuka Kinen,

00:07:31.650 --> 00:07:35.050
it looks like the Kikkashou winner,
Kitasan Black,

00:07:35.050 --> 00:07:38.740
who has improved a fair bit while you were
recuperating, will also be running.

00:07:38.740 --> 00:07:40.710
Both of you have two G1 victories,

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.060
and this will be a battle
of the generational rivals.

00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:44.230
Do you have any thoughts on that?

00:07:44.230 --> 00:07:46.370
I don't care who I'm racing against.

00:07:46.950 --> 00:07:51.320
She's saying the Takarazuka Kinen has
many talented horse girls running in it,

00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:53.950
which is why she's really anticipating it—

00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:57.580
These races are nothing more than stepping
stones to the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:00.410
I intend to prove that I am so superlative,

00:08:00.410 --> 00:08:03.300
with superiority that is obvious to anyone,

00:08:03.300 --> 00:08:05.710
that the words "strong" and
"fast" aren't sufficient.

00:08:05.710 --> 00:08:07.690
Hey! Where are you going, Dura?!

00:08:07.690 --> 00:08:09.090
The interview's not over yet!

00:08:09.390 --> 00:08:11.740
I'm heading back to train, Groovy Sis.

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:14.730
D-Don't call me that when we're on camera!

00:08:14.730 --> 00:08:16.410
Hey, get back here!

00:08:15.690 --> 00:08:18.280
Uh... cut. Stop the camera!

00:08:16.880 --> 00:08:19.010
Did you hear that bit at the end?

00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:19.010
We'll be right back

00:08:19.010 --> 00:08:22.320
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe...
That sounds like Duramente, all right.

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:23.520
This is gonna be good!

00:08:26.750 --> 00:08:29.530
Well, that was a pretty crazy interview.

00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:30.690
It was...

00:08:30.690 --> 00:08:34.260
I can't believe she said all other
races are stepping stones to the

00:08:34.260 --> 00:08:35.280
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:08:35.280 --> 00:08:36.470
She did...

00:08:37.030 --> 00:08:39.420
I mean, I get where she's coming from!

00:08:39.420 --> 00:08:42.790
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe is one
of the biggest races in the world!

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:46.420
I guess that's hard to understand
if you've never run in it!

00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:49.300
You're not gonna just take
all that, are you, Kitasan?!

00:08:49.300 --> 00:08:50.050
She's right!

00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:52.290
You had better not lose to that rude girl!

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:55.230
R-Right! I absolutely, definitely won't lose!

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:58.510
Or so I'd like to say, but...

00:08:58.930 --> 00:09:03.180
Duramente-san really is strong.

00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:05.190
Yeah...

00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:08.710
At the Satsukishou, she was
kinda rough around the edges,

00:09:08.710 --> 00:09:11.850
but you could feel this kinda
unfathomable strength too.

00:09:11.850 --> 00:09:12.850
You could...

00:09:12.850 --> 00:09:17.580
And when her talents fully came
into bloom, she dominated the Derby.

00:09:17.580 --> 00:09:18.800
She did...

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:23.270
Duramente-san didn't run in the
Kikkashou or Spring Tennoushou.

00:09:23.610 --> 00:09:27.210
I've never won against her before.

00:09:27.210 --> 00:09:29.960
But the person she beat
was last year's Kitasan.

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:31.970
Am I right?

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:35.160
That's right! You've gotten
way stronger, Kita-chan!

00:09:35.160 --> 00:09:36.130
You have.

00:09:36.130 --> 00:09:40.080
You've grown a full size since then.
You're practically a different person.

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:40.890
You are.

00:09:42.330 --> 00:09:43.190
Check it!

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Takarazuka Kinen

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Fan Vote

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Kitasan Black

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Bravo Day

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Elegant General

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
All Haiyu

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Seventh Queen

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:50.650
Duramente

00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:52.310
You managed to defend my number one spot
in the fan vote! Well done, apprentice!

00:09:52.310 --> 00:09:54.530
Seriously, since when is she your apprentice?

00:09:54.530 --> 00:09:57.230
What're you gonna do if she starts
running while making stupid faces?

00:09:57.230 --> 00:10:00.430
Eighty-two thousand votes... That's so many.

00:10:00.430 --> 00:10:02.420
Everyone's got high hopes for you.

00:10:02.420 --> 00:10:07.580
For Kitasan Black, who won the
Kikkashou and Spring Tennoushou.

00:10:15.030 --> 00:10:16.170
Everyone...

00:10:38.110 --> 00:10:43.620
Oh, what do I do? I didn't bring an umbrella.

00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:47.040
Oh, man... oh, man.

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:48.550
Oh, man...

00:10:58.970 --> 00:11:02.970
Umamusume

00:10:58.970 --> 00:11:02.970
Pretty Derby

00:11:14.490 --> 00:11:16.820
W-Well...

00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.620
Doesn't look like it's letting up, huh?

00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:22.300
Yeah.

00:11:26.990 --> 00:11:30.660
I, uh... forgot my umbrella.

00:11:31.370 --> 00:11:33.770
You too, Duramente-san?

00:11:34.280 --> 00:11:35.040
Yeah.

00:11:35.870 --> 00:11:37.530
I guess we're in the same boat.

00:11:46.830 --> 00:11:50.230
So... I saw your interview.

00:11:50.740 --> 00:11:53.800
You're pretty amazing, Duramente-san.

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:58.900
Saying that you'd prove your
superiority with such confidence...

00:12:00.030 --> 00:12:02.510
You're not... scared at all?

00:12:03.160 --> 00:12:08.740
Of like... losing, or not living
up to everyone's expectations?

00:12:09.350 --> 00:12:10.930
I've never thought about it.

00:12:13.160 --> 00:12:16.130
You really are amazing.

00:12:16.870 --> 00:12:19.010
Because I have a duty.

00:12:20.700 --> 00:12:22.000
My family has always pursued

00:12:22.430 --> 00:12:25.360
a distant dream of taking on the
most extreme challenges.

00:12:26.330 --> 00:12:29.010
That's in my blood.

00:12:29.640 --> 00:12:34.200
At the end of my path of conquest
is proof that I am the strongest...

00:12:34.620 --> 00:12:35.920
the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:12:36.400 --> 00:12:39.520
My reason for being is to win there.

00:12:39.850 --> 00:12:44.670
Even if I lose, I can't afford to hesitate.

00:12:46.260 --> 00:12:48.960
I'm here to collect something I lost.

00:12:49.820 --> 00:12:53.740
I was unable to run in the Kikkashou.

00:12:54.780 --> 00:12:55.640
That's all.

00:12:56.470 --> 00:12:58.930
I am still the strongest of my generation.

00:12:59.290 --> 00:13:02.970
By beating the Kikkashou's winner,
I will prove that.

00:13:03.420 --> 00:13:06.930
And then I will take on the world,
and win the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:18.590
Wanting to chase after a dream...

00:13:18.590 --> 00:13:20.670
A heart that never hesitates...

00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:25.390
Such a forthright, beautiful...
and strong person.

00:13:25.950 --> 00:13:30.920
Duramente-san entered the Takarazuka
Kinen to race against me!

00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:33.570
But...

00:13:34.450 --> 00:13:39.790
I've eaten and trained a lot to
get stronger this year, too.

00:13:40.060 --> 00:13:42.800
So I hope you don't think it'll be easy!

00:13:45.590 --> 00:13:46.810
Who are you?

00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:50.140
Excuse me?

00:13:51.040 --> 00:13:52.190
Who are you?

00:13:53.910 --> 00:13:58.080
Uh... do you not know who I am?

00:13:58.080 --> 00:13:58.810
I don't.

00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:05.940
K-Kitasan Black! I'm the
Kikkashou winner! That's me!

00:14:06.340 --> 00:14:07.340
I see.

00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:12.120
Duramente-san!

00:14:12.700 --> 00:14:14.040
I'll show you the way I race!

00:14:14.040 --> 00:14:18.580
The way that Kitasan Black, the
horse girl who'll beat you, runs!

00:14:18.580 --> 00:14:21.990
See you at the Takarazuka Kinen!

00:14:34.850 --> 00:14:37.670
I was totally beneath her notice!

00:14:37.670 --> 00:14:39.100
So I'll hit her with everything I've got!

00:14:39.100 --> 00:14:42.650
Everything that's changed
about me since last year!

00:14:48.650 --> 00:14:49.890
Dia.

00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:51.660
I won't let you face this alone!

00:14:51.660 --> 00:14:56.160
The Satono jinx... next time, I'll break it!

00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:00.610
I'll show them...

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:04.900
the moment that I seize a grand victory.

00:15:04.900 --> 00:15:07.180
To my sisters!

00:15:22.740 --> 00:15:27.310
Here they are, proud to be chosen by
fans and dedicated to their dreams.

00:15:27.310 --> 00:15:28.930
We've got a blue sky in the early summer

00:15:28.930 --> 00:15:32.450
here at the Hanshin Racecourse,
with 17 horse girls waiting.

00:15:32.700 --> 00:15:36.200
It's the grand prix race that ends the first
half of the year, the Takarazuka Kinen!

00:15:36.200 --> 00:15:38.080
And it's beginning soon!

00:15:38.310 --> 00:15:43.080
Duramente and Kitasan Black will be colliding,
both of them having won two G1 races.

00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:46.020
Kitasan Black was in first
place in the fan vote,

00:15:46.020 --> 00:15:48.220
but Duramente is the favorite to win today!

00:15:48.220 --> 00:15:51.680
It's been a year since
their last confrontation.

00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:56.250
It should be interesting to see
how they've both grown as racers.

00:16:00.010 --> 00:16:02.570
The course condition is
looking good and soft.

00:16:02.570 --> 00:16:06.980
Yeah. Kitasan's power and stamina will
definitely give her an advantage.

00:16:07.430 --> 00:16:09.990
But she's up against a real monster...

00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:12.230
Don't get psyched out, Kitasan!

00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:41.980
The festival girl, Kitasan Black,
and the returning monster, Duramente.

00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:44.910
Which one will come out on top?

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:46.970
They run now carrying the fans' dreams,

00:16:46.970 --> 00:16:51.080
with their own dreams of taking on the
world here at the Takarazuka Kinen!

00:16:52.030 --> 00:16:54.610
And off they go!

00:16:56.780 --> 00:16:58.890
There's already a fight for first place!

00:16:58.890 --> 00:17:00.640
Kitasan Black is off to a good start.

00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:02.770
She's in the lead and setting the pace!

00:17:02.770 --> 00:17:03.830
Okay!

00:17:03.830 --> 00:17:05.420
They're entering the first home stretch.

00:17:05.420 --> 00:17:08.330
You can hear the cheers of this
crowd greeting them on their return!

00:17:08.330 --> 00:17:10.090
Kitasan Black!

00:17:10.090 --> 00:17:11.840
Go!

00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:13.600
Kitasan Black is in the lead.

00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:15.560
Fighting for second place
is number four, Two-and-Lonely,

00:17:15.560 --> 00:17:18.440
number 10, Canon Mille-feuille,
and number five, Cheval Grand!

00:17:18.440 --> 00:17:22.050
Duramente is towards the back of
the middle, fourth from last place.

00:17:22.050 --> 00:17:25.100
Satono Crown is behind her as
they round the first corner!

00:17:25.460 --> 00:17:28.100
Kitasan is on the run.
Duramente is laying in wait.

00:17:28.100 --> 00:17:29.710
We're seeing a real contrast in their styles.

00:17:29.710 --> 00:17:31.960
In first place, Kitasan Black
has a two-length lead.

00:17:31.960 --> 00:17:34.860
Coming around the second corner,
they're entering a straightaway.

00:17:35.130 --> 00:17:38.380
Second place is between number four,
Two-And-Lonely, and number 10, Canon Mille-feuille,

00:17:38.380 --> 00:17:41.740
with number 11, Nanpo Fox on the
outside, and then Cheval Grand!

00:17:41.740 --> 00:17:44.420
Towards the back of the
mid-section is where the monster

00:17:44.420 --> 00:17:46.750
aiming to prey on the world,
Duramente, awaits!

00:17:46.750 --> 00:17:48.170
Satono Crown is behind her!

00:17:49.500 --> 00:17:52.250
They've crossed 1,000 meters in
the second lap in 59.1 seconds!

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:53.430
That's under a minute!

00:17:53.430 --> 00:17:54.910
Seems kinda fast.

00:17:54.910 --> 00:17:56.110
It does.

00:17:56.110 --> 00:17:56.880
But...

00:17:56.880 --> 00:18:00.390
Kitasan should be able to keep
going through to the end now.

00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:01.350
As the race enters its second half,

00:18:01.350 --> 00:18:03.440
will Kitasan Black be able to
stay out in front to the end?

00:18:03.440 --> 00:18:06.890
During the Derby, I could
only see in front of me...

00:18:07.150 --> 00:18:08.780
But now I can tell.

00:18:08.780 --> 00:18:10.610
I can feel the others gaining on me...

00:18:11.150 --> 00:18:13.650
And hear Duramente-san's footsteps!

00:18:13.650 --> 00:18:16.150
Kitasan Black has the lead by one length!

00:18:16.150 --> 00:18:19.720
But entering the fourth corner, number
16, River Light, is moving up!

00:18:19.720 --> 00:18:21.980
While Duramente remains
in the middle of the pack!

00:18:21.980 --> 00:18:25.060
I'm not out of breath...
my legs feel light...

00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:28.040
I'm going to show them how I run—and win!

00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:28.640
Now!

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:29.540
It's on!

00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:32.650
And exiting the last corner,
they enter the straight!

00:18:32.650 --> 00:18:35.260
Kitasan Black is in front
with a two-lengths lead!

00:18:35.260 --> 00:18:37.200
Second place is number seven, Bravo Day,

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.070
with number 16, River Light, on the outside!

00:18:39.070 --> 00:18:42.930
After them is Cheval Grand, with Satono
Crown accelerating on the far edge!

00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.210
Go, Kita-chan!

00:18:44.210 --> 00:18:45.770
Push through to the end!

00:18:45.770 --> 00:18:47.380
There are 200 meters left!

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:48.770
They begin to ascend a hill!

00:18:48.770 --> 00:18:50.460
And... here she comes!

00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:53.690
Dashing through the pack is the monstrous
Duramente, aiming for the lead!

00:18:53.690 --> 00:18:54.270
She's coming!

00:18:55.110 --> 00:18:56.920
I have to stay in front!

00:19:05.010 --> 00:19:08.170
There's Duramente! But is she struggling?!

00:19:08.170 --> 00:19:10.460
Kitasan Black maintains her lead!

00:19:12.850 --> 00:19:13.670
She's fast.

00:19:13.970 --> 00:19:16.210
But I will pass her!

00:19:16.210 --> 00:19:17.800
Kitasan Black in front!

00:19:17.800 --> 00:19:19.880
But Duramente is barreling ever closer!

00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:22.890
I'll prove I'm the strongest!

00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:50.250
Who?!

00:19:51.870 --> 00:19:54.290
River Light comes flying in!

00:19:54.290 --> 00:19:56.300
It's River Light!

00:19:57.590 --> 00:20:02.880
The victory doesn't go to the festival
or the monster, but to River Light!

00:20:05.600 --> 00:20:07.600
She managed to pass Kitasan Black,
who was on the inside,

00:20:07.600 --> 00:20:11.100
along with Duramente on the outside!

00:20:11.450 --> 00:20:15.600
This grand prix has been won
by number 16, River Light!

00:20:18.170 --> 00:20:20.220
I did it! I did it!

00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:22.360
I really, really did it!

00:20:22.360 --> 00:20:24.130
I lost again...

00:20:33.960 --> 00:20:35.300
Duramente-san?!

00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:38.180
Duramente-san, are you okay?

00:20:38.590 --> 00:20:40.610
Uh... let's get you to the doctor's office...

00:20:40.610 --> 00:20:41.420
It's fine.

00:20:41.420 --> 00:20:42.330
But—

00:20:42.330 --> 00:20:43.310
It's fine!

00:21:02.410 --> 00:21:05.550
You really are amazing, Duramente-san.

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:07.420
You managed to pass me again.

00:21:08.110 --> 00:21:09.640
I completely lost.

00:21:09.640 --> 00:21:10.820
I won!

00:21:10.820 --> 00:21:12.300
You were strong.

00:21:13.610 --> 00:21:16.170
You forced me to run the way I did.

00:21:17.650 --> 00:21:21.800
I thought you were just a stepping stone,
but there was a real point to this.

00:21:22.170 --> 00:21:25.190
I'm glad I ran in this Takarazuka Kinen.

00:21:23.360 --> 00:21:24.740
I actually won!

00:21:26.560 --> 00:21:28.470
I'm going to get even stronger.

00:21:28.870 --> 00:21:33.010
And next time, I will dominate you,
Kitasan Black.

00:21:35.030 --> 00:21:36.590
Duramente-san...

00:21:37.150 --> 00:21:38.410
Well, me too!

00:21:38.940 --> 00:21:42.010
I'm gonna get way, way stronger, too!

00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:45.420
And next time, I'm not
gonna lose, Duramente-san!

00:21:45.420 --> 00:21:46.400
Nah...

00:21:46.950 --> 00:21:49.450
I'm not gonna lose, Dura-chan!

00:21:47.710 --> 00:21:49.450
Thank you!

00:21:50.660 --> 00:21:52.450
Dura... chan?

00:21:52.450 --> 00:21:54.450
Yeah! Dura-chan!

00:21:57.850 --> 00:21:58.610
All right.

00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:02.180
Yes!

00:22:04.970 --> 00:22:07.000
Thanks for rooting for me!

00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:08.170
Damn...

00:22:08.170 --> 00:22:11.980
They were second and third place.
What could they be talking about?

00:22:12.305 --> 00:23:12.633
